Wire the cgo sds-go binding to the bazel-provided libdd_sds.

Gazelle infers `clinkopts = ["-L../../sds/target/release -ldd_sds"]` from the
`#cgo LDFLAGS` directive in build.go. That relative -L path is meaningless under
bazel's sandbox and nothing provides libdd_sds, so GoCompilePkg fails with
`cannot find -ldd_sds`. Replace the clinkopt with a cdeps edge onto
//deps/sds:dd_sds, which wraps the prebuilt shared library. That cc_library is
itself marked incompatible on Windows (where SDS is unsupported), and the
incompatibility propagates back through this cdeps edge so the whole sds chain
is skipped in `//...` on Windows.

This patch is applied by go_deps.module_override *after* gazelle generates the
BUILD file, so it edits the generated output directly.
--- a/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/BUILD.bazel
@@ -45,7 +45,7 @@
         "validation.go",
     ],
     cgo = True,
-    clinkopts = ["-L../../sds/target/release -ldd_sds"],
+    cdeps = ["@@//deps/sds:dd_sds"],
     importpath = "github.com/DataDog/dd-sensitive-data-scanner/sds-go/go",
     visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
 )
